SYNOPSIS
========
   int write_file(string file, string str           )
   int write_file(string file, string str, int flags)

DESCRIPTION
===========
   Append the string str(E) to the file file(E). Returns 1 for success and 0 
   if any failure occured.

   If flags(E) is 1, the file is removed first; thus making the 'append' 
   effectively an 'overwrite'. Default for flags(E) is 0.

HISTORY
=======
   - changed (3.3.523) -- added the flags(E) parameter.

SEE ALSO
========
   file_size(E), write_bytes(E), write_file(E), read_file(E), read_bytes(E), 
   rm(E), get_dir(E)
